<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Splicer" class="currentChild" href="Splicer">Splicer</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In <a title="Web Offset Lithography" href="Web_Offset_Lithography">web offset lithography</a>, a device attached to the <a title="Roll Stand" href="Roll_Stand">roll stand</a> of a web press which automatically splices a new paper roll to the end of an expiring roll. A splicer may either be a <a title="Flying Splicer" href="Flying_Splicer">flying splicer</a> or a <a title="Zero-Speed Splicer" href="Zero-Speed_Splicer">zero-speed splicer</a>. See <a title="Web Offset Lithography: Infeed and Web Control: Splicing" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/Web_Offset_Lithography:_Infeed_and_Web_Control:_Splicing">Web Offset Lithography: Infeed and Web Control: Splicing</a>. Also known as a <a title="Paster" href="Paster">paster</a>. 
</p>
